WEBVTT

00:07.094 --> 00:09.139
♪ ♪

00:19.845 --> 00:23.110
[Dr. Goodbee]
Your son had a serious
electrical event.

00:23.153 --> 00:25.199
He's had some...

00:25.242 --> 00:27.549
neurological complications.

00:27.592 --> 00:30.378
We'd like to keep him here
for a few days, run some tests.

00:31.683 --> 00:33.468
[Dot]
I want a moment alone

00:33.511 --> 00:34.991
with my husband.

00:35.035 --> 00:37.167
Why, so you can get
your stories straight?

00:37.211 --> 00:38.473
Get out.

00:45.610 --> 00:47.482
[Dot]
Listen, bitch.

00:47.525 --> 00:50.615
I've climbed through six kinds
of hell to get where I am,

00:50.659 --> 00:52.965
and no Ivy League royal wannabe

00:53.009 --> 00:54.184
is gonna run me off just because

00:54.228 --> 00:55.751
she doesn't like
the way I smell.

00:58.014 --> 01:00.277
[Danish]
What about Dorothy?

01:00.321 --> 01:01.757
[Lorraine] She's a wolf
in sheep's clothing,

01:01.800 --> 01:04.412
that one.
We keep her close for now.

01:13.073 --> 01:15.118
♪ ♪

01:33.397 --> 01:38.228
[narrator]
The tiger, spelled T-I-G-E-R,

01:38.272 --> 01:41.753
is one of the fiercest hunters
on Earth.

01:41.797 --> 01:44.104
-[Lorraine] I have
to run into the city.
-[Danish] Oh.

01:44.147 --> 01:45.540
[Lorraine]
It's in place?

01:45.583 --> 01:47.542
-What we discussed?
-It is.

01:47.585 --> 01:49.631
But I feel I must reiterate--

01:49.674 --> 01:51.981
Yes, yes, you went on
at length last night.

01:52.024 --> 01:54.201
It's funny how
one's tireless moralizing

01:54.244 --> 01:55.854
can become so tiring.

01:55.898 --> 01:58.596
You have power of attorney,
don't you?

01:58.640 --> 02:01.425
In cases where both she and
her husband are incapacitated.

02:02.426 --> 02:04.080
Well, there you go.

02:04.124 --> 02:05.821
[narrator]
Known for its cunning

02:05.864 --> 02:07.736
and strategic mind,

02:07.779 --> 02:09.999
the tiger is most dangerous

02:10.042 --> 02:11.653
when cornered.

02:11.696 --> 02:13.350
Dorothy.

02:14.351 --> 02:16.353
Dorothy.

02:17.789 --> 02:19.443
What time is it?

02:19.487 --> 02:21.576
Just past 11:00.

02:21.619 --> 02:23.360
-[Dot] Mm.
-These men

02:23.404 --> 02:25.580
would like to talk to you.

02:25.623 --> 02:27.495
What?

02:34.632 --> 02:36.199
[Early]
Relax, Dorothy.

02:36.243 --> 02:38.506
We just want to talk to you.

02:38.549 --> 02:40.769
[Danish]
It's for your own good, Dorothy.

02:40.812 --> 02:43.032
It's for your protection.

02:43.075 --> 02:44.729
[faintly]
We're very concerned...

02:44.773 --> 02:46.557
[screams] No!

02:46.601 --> 02:49.125
[Danish]
The last few days,
with all the upset, and...

02:49.169 --> 02:50.431
[screams]

02:50.474 --> 02:52.868
[Danish]
Mrs. Lyon, Lorraine...

02:52.911 --> 02:54.522
Liars. No.

02:54.565 --> 02:56.001
Hmm. No!

02:56.045 --> 02:58.265
I don't agree to this.
[screams]

02:58.308 --> 03:00.789
[Danish]
...she feels-- and I agree--

03:00.832 --> 03:02.138
you've been having some kind

03:02.182 --> 03:03.966
of psychotic...

03:04.009 --> 03:07.535
Oh, okay, well, maybe
that's too strong a word.

03:07.578 --> 03:10.146
You're fired.

03:10.190 --> 03:12.104
We're worried that
you've become a danger

03:12.148 --> 03:14.150
to yourself or others.

03:14.194 --> 03:16.108
You're the danger.

03:16.152 --> 03:17.762
My lawyer?

03:17.806 --> 03:19.503
My A-S-S.

03:19.547 --> 03:21.288
If you take me,

03:21.331 --> 03:23.594
I'm gonna try and blind
you boys, break your fingers,

03:23.638 --> 03:25.683
bite off both your noses.

03:25.727 --> 03:28.077
Dorothy.

03:28.120 --> 03:30.384
Ah-ah. Maybe you heard the story

03:30.427 --> 03:32.299
where I burned a fella alive,

03:32.342 --> 03:34.779
chopped the other one's ear off

03:34.823 --> 03:36.651
when they came for me.

03:37.652 --> 03:39.523
I'm not saying that's true...

03:41.395 --> 03:43.353
...but if you try to force me
against my will...

03:44.963 --> 03:46.313
...you're gonna find out.

03:46.356 --> 03:48.184
[chuckles]

03:54.234 --> 03:55.800
I told you.

04:02.198 --> 04:03.417
[grunts]

04:07.072 --> 04:09.161
[ambulance doors close]

04:14.645 --> 04:16.256
Shoot.

04:20.825 --> 04:22.349
It's done.

04:25.613 --> 04:27.267
[sighs]

04:39.583 --> 04:41.281
Okay.

04:41.324 --> 04:43.892
Well, here we go.
Home away from home.

04:43.935 --> 04:46.938
-I'm feeling much better now.
-Oh, good.

04:46.982 --> 04:49.332
-I mean it.
-Oh, well, uh...

04:49.376 --> 04:51.116
-good.
-[chuckles]

04:51.160 --> 04:52.117
[Dot]
I just think,

04:52.161 --> 04:54.250
to go to all this trouble,

04:54.294 --> 04:55.860
so much fuss,

04:55.904 --> 04:57.862
when all I need is a bath

04:57.906 --> 05:01.083
and, you know,
Calgon, take me away.

05:01.126 --> 05:03.433
Yeah. Okay.

05:05.305 --> 05:07.655
-[elevator bell dings]
-And you're so busy.

05:07.698 --> 05:09.657
-I hate to keep you.
-[Danish] Dorothy.

05:09.700 --> 05:11.615
No.

05:11.659 --> 05:15.445
And I am so sorry
for biting you boys.

05:15.489 --> 05:16.881
[elevator bell dings]

05:21.625 --> 05:23.671
[indistinct chatter]

05:37.075 --> 05:40.122
[narrator]
Though it may look like
the tiger has given up,

05:40.165 --> 05:42.820
this is, in fact, a ruse.

05:42.864 --> 05:45.040
Look closer.

05:45.083 --> 05:47.042
Even now, she plans an escape.

05:47.085 --> 05:49.958
[door creaks open]

05:50.915 --> 05:52.352
What a day.

05:53.614 --> 05:56.530
I'm sorry. I mean it.

05:56.573 --> 05:59.402
Geez, I must look a fright.
[chuckles]

05:59.446 --> 06:02.013
Mascara down my face,
my nose running.

06:02.057 --> 06:04.668
I'm so embarrassed.

06:04.712 --> 06:06.670
You wouldn't have a hanky,
would you?

06:09.020 --> 06:10.065
Yeah, I--

06:10.108 --> 06:11.762
[screaming]

06:12.676 --> 06:13.808
[both grunting]

06:28.736 --> 06:30.868
Here we are.

06:32.000 --> 06:34.089
[indistinct chatter]

06:58.330 --> 07:01.116
I'm so glad we could do this.

07:01.159 --> 07:04.467
The numbers look good.
Rupert ran them yesterday.

07:04.511 --> 07:06.600
Yeah, pretty sweet.

07:06.643 --> 07:09.951
Says he's been talking things
through with your Mr. Graves.

07:09.994 --> 07:11.561
Thought he'd be here.

07:11.605 --> 07:14.434
Well, he's not.
You get the headliner.

07:14.477 --> 07:16.044
[Vivian]
Rupert says he likes him.

07:16.087 --> 07:18.525
-Straight shooter.
-Says he trusts him.

07:18.568 --> 07:20.744
I'm so glad.

07:23.660 --> 07:25.749
Thought we'd see him today.

07:27.664 --> 07:29.753
Let me guess,

07:29.797 --> 07:33.104
the last time you negotiated
with a woman

07:33.148 --> 07:36.717
was over the price
of a Tijuana blowjob.

07:36.760 --> 07:39.154
How much to...

07:39.197 --> 07:41.896
stick it in your asshole,
that kind of thing.

07:41.939 --> 07:43.767
I'll have the Cobb salad,
no cheese,

07:43.811 --> 07:46.117
and I'm guessing

07:46.161 --> 07:48.250
burger and fries for these boys.

07:48.293 --> 07:50.382
And bring us
a bottle of the Caymus,

07:50.426 --> 07:52.950
the '92, not the '93.

07:54.125 --> 07:55.605
Goodbye.

07:57.041 --> 07:58.434
Now, Miss--

07:58.478 --> 08:01.481
Mrs. Lorraine Lyon.

08:01.524 --> 08:04.396
CEO of Redemption Services,

08:04.440 --> 08:06.137
a Nasdaq-listed,

08:06.181 --> 08:09.227
multibillion dollar
corporation.

08:10.577 --> 08:13.014
Mrs. Lyon has six governors

08:13.057 --> 08:15.495
on speed dial
and her own personal

08:15.538 --> 08:17.932
liaison at
the Federal Trade Commission.

08:17.975 --> 08:20.064
Nice to meet you.

08:20.108 --> 08:22.589
Are we friends yet? Good.

08:24.242 --> 08:26.723
I want to buy your bank,

08:26.767 --> 08:29.552
but, more important,
you need to sell your bank

08:29.596 --> 08:32.033
because I looked
at your numbers,

08:32.076 --> 08:34.905
and you don't have enough
cash on hand to satisfy current

08:34.949 --> 08:37.952
U.S. banking regulations,
which...

08:38.996 --> 08:41.129
...one phone call from me,

08:41.172 --> 08:45.002
and you will have so many
SEC agents up your keister,

08:45.046 --> 08:48.310
you'll be shitting briefcases
for the rest of your life.

08:48.353 --> 08:50.965
Now hold on just a second, lady.

08:51.008 --> 08:52.009
Do you see?

08:52.053 --> 08:53.837
Right there.

08:53.881 --> 08:55.360
I'm going to knock 10 million

08:55.404 --> 08:57.667
off my offer
because you called me "lady."

08:57.711 --> 08:59.582
We just--

08:59.626 --> 09:01.366
Pipe down, pony boy.

09:01.410 --> 09:04.065
I'll tell you
when it's your turn to talk.

09:05.719 --> 09:08.199
I'm willing

09:08.243 --> 09:10.767
to buy your shady

09:10.811 --> 09:13.596
five-gallon bank...

09:14.728 --> 09:17.339
...because I'm
in the debt business,

09:17.382 --> 09:19.994
and I want to get
into the credit business.

09:20.037 --> 09:22.083
Everyone loves a lender,

09:22.126 --> 09:24.476
not so much the repo man,

09:24.520 --> 09:26.435
but I need to test the waters,

09:26.478 --> 09:29.220
make sure the government'll
let me do both,

09:29.264 --> 09:32.093
so I'm starting small,

09:32.136 --> 09:33.703
with you.

09:33.747 --> 09:36.663
And I'm willing to pay a premium

09:36.706 --> 09:38.360
to get this done quickly,

09:38.403 --> 09:41.058
but if you hate women

09:41.102 --> 09:42.843
more than you love money,

09:42.886 --> 09:46.411
I'll just take
my millions elsewhere.

09:47.848 --> 09:49.501
Enjoy the wine.

09:50.807 --> 09:54.506
I expect your answer
by end of business today.

09:57.466 --> 09:59.555
♪ ♪

10:15.049 --> 10:16.572
Hey.

10:16.616 --> 10:18.792
Hear it's supposed
to snow later, hmm?

10:18.835 --> 10:21.708
Here's me putting off
changing out the radials

10:21.751 --> 10:23.535
-till the last second.
-You're not Sarah.

10:23.579 --> 10:26.060
-Oh.
-Where's Sarah?

10:27.409 --> 10:29.367
It's my first day.

10:29.411 --> 10:31.979
Still haven't got all the names
straight. [chuckles]

10:32.022 --> 10:34.024
Sarah's the one with...

10:38.812 --> 10:40.988
-[alarm ringing]
-Oh.

10:45.079 --> 10:47.298
[woman over P.A.]
Code gray on floor two.

10:47.342 --> 10:49.736
Security,
please report to floor two.

10:49.779 --> 10:51.912
Code gray.

10:51.955 --> 10:54.479
[indistinct radio chatter]

10:54.523 --> 10:56.568
There you are. Hi.

10:56.612 --> 10:58.962
Okay. Mm...

11:21.202 --> 11:22.899
What now?

11:31.908 --> 11:33.475
Mrs. Lyon.

11:33.518 --> 11:36.652
Let me guess,
the orphans need a new roof.

11:36.696 --> 11:38.654
Well, probably,
but I'm more of a

11:38.698 --> 11:41.048
"let the orphans fight each
other for sport" kind of guy.

11:41.091 --> 11:42.571
Libertarian, so...

11:43.746 --> 11:45.269
I've got a busy day, Officer.

11:45.313 --> 11:47.445
It's "sheriff," actually.

11:47.489 --> 11:49.491
Roy Tillman,
from over Stark County.

11:49.534 --> 11:51.493
North Dakota.

11:51.536 --> 11:55.410
That's the one.
I was hoping we could, uh, talk.

11:55.453 --> 11:59.153
Uh-huh. And what exactly
are we talking about?

11:59.196 --> 12:01.503
Uh, well, your daughter-in-law.

12:01.546 --> 12:03.374
Well, what's she done now?

12:03.418 --> 12:04.854
She married me.

12:07.465 --> 12:09.990
[stammers]
You better come inside.

12:21.131 --> 12:23.917
[sighs] Okay, sailor.

12:23.960 --> 12:25.832
What are you gonna cost me?

12:25.875 --> 12:26.963
Excuse me?

12:27.007 --> 12:28.486
The "fuck off fee."

12:28.530 --> 12:30.662
Never to be seen again.

12:32.055 --> 12:34.318
[sighs] Oh... Good God,

12:34.362 --> 12:36.668
don't tell me you want her back.

12:37.800 --> 12:39.367
Is it just the money,

12:39.410 --> 12:41.151
or have you always been
this high and mighty?

12:41.195 --> 12:43.153
Like that,
looking down your nose

12:43.197 --> 12:45.025
on a hard-working American.

12:45.068 --> 12:47.679
And me with my hat in hand
just trying to do what's right.

12:47.723 --> 12:49.551
What's right for whom?

12:49.594 --> 12:51.988
Right as in the Bible,

12:52.032 --> 12:55.078
as in a woman swears an oath
to honor and obey her man,

12:55.122 --> 12:57.298
not go out and get a six-pack
and never come home.

12:57.341 --> 12:59.300
May I have the details

12:59.343 --> 13:01.606
of this alleged matrimony,
please?

13:06.524 --> 13:10.006
June 3, 2007.
We got married at the ranch.

13:10.050 --> 13:12.356
My second, her first. Uh...

13:12.400 --> 13:14.271
We were together about

13:14.315 --> 13:16.578
two years, before and during,
and then, all of a sudden,

13:16.621 --> 13:19.711
poof, she disappears. [sighs]

13:19.755 --> 13:21.626
Gone.

13:22.802 --> 13:24.499
Well, I'll tell you,
there were nights

13:24.542 --> 13:26.457
I figured she must've been dead.

13:26.501 --> 13:28.024
Horrible thoughts.

13:28.068 --> 13:30.679
Mountain lions, Mexican rapists.

13:32.376 --> 13:34.291
So you can understand my relief

13:34.335 --> 13:36.685
when the report came in
said she'd been found.

13:36.728 --> 13:39.906
Uh-huh.

13:39.949 --> 13:42.778
Yeah, my first thought hearing
that she'd remarried with a kid,

13:42.822 --> 13:45.215
maybe some sort of amnesia.

13:45.259 --> 13:47.087
Found wandering the highway,

13:47.130 --> 13:48.697
not knowing
when her birthday f--

13:48.740 --> 13:51.395
All right, I-I...
I get the picture.

13:51.439 --> 13:53.702
Listen, slick.

13:53.745 --> 13:56.444
Nothing would make me happier

13:56.487 --> 13:58.446
than to put that girl in a box

13:58.489 --> 14:00.230
marked "return to sender,"

14:00.274 --> 14:02.929
between you and me, but

14:02.972 --> 14:05.366
she's married to my son,

14:05.409 --> 14:07.194
and he loves her,

14:07.237 --> 14:09.326
and she's the mother
to my granddaughter,

14:09.370 --> 14:11.111
whom I'm fond of,

14:11.154 --> 14:13.591
so you need to put
your big boy pants on

14:13.635 --> 14:15.332
and take the hit.

14:15.376 --> 14:17.857
Bible says the wife
is the property of the husband.

14:17.900 --> 14:19.946
Therefore, that makes your son

14:19.989 --> 14:21.817
a thief.

14:21.861 --> 14:23.645
If we're talking about who has

14:23.688 --> 14:25.342
the more legitimate claim.

14:25.386 --> 14:28.171
You know, I've heard of you.

14:30.347 --> 14:34.090
You're one of those
constitutional sheriffs.

14:34.134 --> 14:35.831
Yes, I am.

14:35.875 --> 14:39.313
Defender of freedom
and protector of the common man

14:39.356 --> 14:42.011
against the tyranny of the state

14:42.055 --> 14:44.057
and all its wicked demands.

14:44.100 --> 14:45.841
-Taxes?
-Oh, yeah.

14:45.885 --> 14:47.451
The social safety net?

14:47.495 --> 14:49.497
Well, I'd spit, but, uh...

14:49.540 --> 14:51.760
Respect for the otherly-abled?

14:51.803 --> 14:53.675
The whole
multi-cultural panoply.

14:53.718 --> 14:56.808
Billy has two mothers,
et cetera, et cetera.

14:56.852 --> 14:58.245
So-so,

14:58.288 --> 15:00.987
you-you want freedom

15:01.030 --> 15:03.424
with no responsibility?

15:04.599 --> 15:06.993
Son, there's only
one person on Earth

15:07.036 --> 15:08.951
-who gets that deal.
-Mm.

15:08.995 --> 15:10.170
The president?

15:11.171 --> 15:12.520
A baby.

15:12.563 --> 15:14.391
[laughs]

15:14.435 --> 15:16.741
You're fighting
for your-your right

15:16.785 --> 15:18.395
to be a baby.

15:19.875 --> 15:22.051
Hi, they said--

15:22.095 --> 15:24.314
Oh, I'm sorry.

15:24.358 --> 15:26.621
I just wanted to check, see
how the powwow went with Duggar.

15:27.665 --> 15:30.451
What is that? Uh, Vivian Dugger?

15:30.494 --> 15:32.627
The banker with a woman's name?

15:32.670 --> 15:34.716
He was in my prowler once.

15:34.759 --> 15:36.979
I caught him in flagrante
with a lady of the evening,

15:37.023 --> 15:38.720
but we came to an arrangement.

15:38.763 --> 15:40.591
That's what reasonable men do.

15:40.635 --> 15:43.725
Should I be-- Do you want me
to sit in on this?

15:43.768 --> 15:45.945
No. No, the, um,

15:45.988 --> 15:48.730
the sheriff was just leaving.

15:48.773 --> 15:50.514
Oh, was I?

15:50.558 --> 15:53.082
Well, as I said, if you're
willing to sign some papers,

15:53.126 --> 15:56.303
I could see my way clear
to writing a check.

15:56.346 --> 15:57.913
I mean,
between your-your reelection

15:57.957 --> 15:59.784
and my business dealings,

15:59.828 --> 16:03.701
I'm sure neither of us want
any sordid details coming out.

16:03.745 --> 16:06.922
Is that reasonable enough
for you?

16:09.838 --> 16:12.319
So, that's who you are.

16:12.362 --> 16:14.974
That's who I am.

16:15.017 --> 16:18.934
And while we're talking
about property rights,

16:18.978 --> 16:21.719
I'd like to be clear that,
after seven years,

16:21.763 --> 16:24.679
a missing person
is presumed dead.

16:24.722 --> 16:27.856
So, technically,

16:27.899 --> 16:31.251
Dorothy is my son's
property now.

16:35.907 --> 16:37.692
Nadine.

16:39.172 --> 16:40.695
Her name's Nadine.

16:40.738 --> 16:42.740
Not anymore.

16:52.315 --> 16:53.969
[sighs]

16:54.013 --> 16:55.797
Women, am I right?

16:57.364 --> 16:59.061
Here's my card.

16:59.105 --> 17:00.802
I'd be happy
to sit down tomorrow,

17:00.845 --> 17:02.586
discuss the details of a deal.

17:04.066 --> 17:06.286
[sighs] Well, son,

17:06.329 --> 17:08.505
I'm not sure
I can negotiate with a man

17:08.549 --> 17:10.290
named after a breakfast pastry.

17:10.333 --> 17:11.508
-[car approaching]
-Yes, well,

17:11.552 --> 17:13.771
I am Mrs. Lyon's

17:13.815 --> 17:15.773
-chief counsel,
so I'm the one you talk to.
-[car door opens, closes]

17:15.817 --> 17:17.210
And who might you be?

17:17.253 --> 17:19.212
Scotty.

17:19.255 --> 17:22.824
He's a muffin, you've got
a boy's name. What's next?

17:22.867 --> 17:25.174
A monkey with a hat? [chuckles]

17:30.136 --> 17:32.355
Nice meeting you there, Scotty.

17:32.399 --> 17:34.575
Tell your mom
Sheriff Roy says hello.

17:34.618 --> 17:37.012
She looks just like her mom.

17:37.056 --> 17:39.058
Yeah. I'll expect your call.

17:39.101 --> 17:41.321
Oh, we'll be seeing
each other again,

17:41.364 --> 17:43.627
just maybe not in the way
you're expecting.

17:43.671 --> 17:45.542
What's that supposed to mean?

17:45.586 --> 17:47.109
You have a nice day.

17:50.330 --> 17:52.419
♪ ♪

17:54.334 --> 17:56.640
Ah...

17:56.684 --> 17:59.034
How many times do I have
to tell you people

17:59.078 --> 18:01.471
-we're not gonna cooperate.
-Mr. Graves,

18:01.515 --> 18:03.256
did you have Dorothy Lyon
committed this morning?

18:03.299 --> 18:05.562
I don't see as that's
any of your business.

18:05.606 --> 18:07.782
Well, it's my business
because she escaped.

18:07.825 --> 18:09.262
Call just went out on the radio.

18:09.305 --> 18:10.437
[chuckles]

18:10.480 --> 18:11.742
That's...

18:18.532 --> 18:20.577
[phone rings]

18:22.101 --> 18:23.667
Talk to me.

18:23.711 --> 18:25.234
[Roy over phone]
Yeah, we're going with plan B.

18:25.278 --> 18:26.627
Take the husband.

18:26.670 --> 18:28.063
Yes.

18:29.108 --> 18:30.848
Yes.

18:30.892 --> 18:32.981
-Pass me to Bowman.
-[Gator] I don't...[sighs]

18:33.024 --> 18:35.549
Pass me to Bowman.

18:35.592 --> 18:38.421
You didn't have to send him
to babysit me.

18:38.465 --> 18:40.075
Just give him the damn phone.

18:40.119 --> 18:42.164
[distant chatter]

18:43.861 --> 18:45.515
Right.

18:51.347 --> 18:52.914
[phone beeps]

18:54.611 --> 18:56.874
What'd he say?

18:56.918 --> 18:58.746
You stay here.

19:01.444 --> 19:02.837
I'm the law.

19:04.055 --> 19:05.535
You...

19:08.190 --> 19:10.149
I'm coming. I'm...

19:14.675 --> 19:16.111
Fuck.

19:17.808 --> 19:21.725
[narrator]
The female, or lady tiger,

19:21.769 --> 19:24.859
can outsmart even
the most skilled hunters.

19:24.902 --> 19:27.775
She is a literal genius
when it comes

19:27.818 --> 19:30.299
to saving her young

19:30.343 --> 19:32.954
and protecting her mate.

19:42.224 --> 19:44.095
What's with all
the extra security?

19:44.139 --> 19:45.793
[clerk]
Oh, a mental patient escaped.

19:45.836 --> 19:48.056
A female.

19:48.099 --> 19:50.058
Mm.

19:50.101 --> 19:52.408
I'm looking for my cousin,
Wayne Lyon.

19:53.496 --> 19:55.150
Aren't we going?

19:55.194 --> 19:57.544
Oh, yeah. We just got to make
a quick stop first.

19:59.372 --> 20:00.851
Come on.

20:00.895 --> 20:02.723
Oh, uh, third floor.

20:02.766 --> 20:05.421
Oh, and, uh, check in
at the nurse's station.

20:07.118 --> 20:08.642
[grunts]

20:08.685 --> 20:10.513
[elevator bell dings]

20:18.260 --> 20:19.914
Hold it.

20:23.091 --> 20:24.310
[sighs]

20:25.354 --> 20:27.313
You stay in the fucking car.

20:27.356 --> 20:28.618
Okay.

20:30.011 --> 20:32.100
You stay in the fucking car.

20:33.232 --> 20:35.277
[mutters]

20:39.281 --> 20:41.327
[exhales]

20:51.902 --> 20:53.643
Shit.

20:56.429 --> 20:58.996
Shit. Shit. Geez.

20:59.040 --> 21:00.389
Uh...

21:15.622 --> 21:17.188
[elevator bell dings]

21:17.232 --> 21:19.278
[indistinct chatter]

21:21.018 --> 21:23.064
[indistinct P.A. announcement]

21:25.066 --> 21:26.763
Just forgot some
of your paperwork, hon.

21:26.807 --> 21:28.243
Back in a jiff.

21:29.549 --> 21:31.986
[indistinct chatter]

21:38.906 --> 21:41.256
Well, about fucking time.

21:41.300 --> 21:43.737
I'm supposed to get
Jell-O and broth.

21:43.780 --> 21:46.870
Hey. They said I could get
some Jell-O and broth.

21:46.914 --> 21:48.611
That's...

21:48.655 --> 21:50.396
Sorry, let me see what I...

21:50.439 --> 21:51.919
[Jordan]
Two days I'm sitting
in this stupid bed

21:51.962 --> 21:53.007
waiting for you people
to rip out

21:53.050 --> 21:54.269
six feet of my intestines.

21:54.313 --> 21:55.444
Least I can do
is get some Jell-O

21:55.488 --> 21:57.403
and fucking broth.

21:57.446 --> 21:59.361
Of course.

21:59.405 --> 22:01.320
I'll check on that for you.

22:01.363 --> 22:02.712
You stealing my coat?

22:02.756 --> 22:04.410
What the hell
kind of place is this?

22:04.453 --> 22:07.021
No. I'm just...

22:07.064 --> 22:09.240
I'm having it cleaned.

22:09.284 --> 22:10.677
It's part of the service
we provide here.

22:10.720 --> 22:12.026
I am on to you, bitch.

22:12.069 --> 22:13.897
All of you people
sneaking around here

22:13.941 --> 22:16.378
pretending you're so nice,
but I know who you really are.

22:16.422 --> 22:18.032
Ow! Ah!

22:18.075 --> 22:19.599
-Ah! Ah!
-Why are you

22:19.642 --> 22:21.514
-so rude? Hmm?
-Ah! Ah! Oh!

22:21.557 --> 22:23.254
-So angry?
-[grunting]

22:23.298 --> 22:25.126
All of you.

22:25.169 --> 22:27.346
Whatever happened
to grace and dignity?

22:27.389 --> 22:29.435
[muffled shouting]

22:31.219 --> 22:33.352
Everybody here
is just trying to help.

22:52.980 --> 22:55.548
[narrator]
The tiger has been known
to set traps

22:55.591 --> 22:57.419
to ensnare her pursuers.

22:57.463 --> 22:59.247
Thus, the popular colloquialism

22:59.290 --> 23:01.554
"Do not hunt the tiger

23:01.597 --> 23:05.035
unless you want the tiger
catching you."

23:09.692 --> 23:10.824
What's money?

23:10.867 --> 23:13.392
Money? That... Oh, hon,

23:13.435 --> 23:15.785
I don't have time to go
into the whole...

23:17.265 --> 23:19.136
Let's get you
to the bathroom, yeah?

23:19.180 --> 23:21.095
Oh, I just went.

23:21.138 --> 23:22.618
Poop came out.

23:22.662 --> 23:24.577
Mm. Oh.

23:24.620 --> 23:26.013
That's good, hon.

23:26.056 --> 23:27.623
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

23:27.667 --> 23:29.320
We're gonna go, though, yeah?

23:29.364 --> 23:31.061
Mm-hmm.

23:31.105 --> 23:33.107
Yeah.

23:33.150 --> 23:34.717
[grunts]

23:35.979 --> 23:38.373
Uh, hold on,
my foot's unconscious.

23:38.417 --> 23:40.593
-Oh.
-Yeah.

23:40.636 --> 23:42.595
-It's okay.
-[grunts]

23:42.638 --> 23:44.510
[grunting]

23:50.298 --> 23:51.908
I love you, too.

23:56.391 --> 23:57.958
Come on.

23:58.001 --> 23:59.263
Mm.

24:00.395 --> 24:03.920
The nurse told me
that we're rich,

24:03.964 --> 24:05.661
and I said I didn't know
what that was.

24:05.705 --> 24:06.749
[Dot chuckles]

24:12.799 --> 24:13.800
What?

24:13.843 --> 24:15.584
Stay here, okay?

24:15.628 --> 24:17.543
Then, you see...

24:19.588 --> 24:21.111
...this lock?

24:22.591 --> 24:23.723
Yeah.

24:23.766 --> 24:25.159
Turn it when I'm gone

24:25.202 --> 24:27.030
and don't come out until I say.

24:36.736 --> 24:38.868
I love you three.

24:40.957 --> 24:43.133
[Dot]
Lock the door, baby.

24:45.919 --> 24:47.311
[lock clicks]

24:58.758 --> 25:00.324
It's this one.

25:04.546 --> 25:05.939
Stay here.

25:14.600 --> 25:16.297
[both gasp]

25:16.340 --> 25:17.646
Oh, Nadine.

25:17.690 --> 25:18.865
-What?
-Dorothy,

25:18.908 --> 25:20.170
he means. Sorry.

25:20.214 --> 25:22.259
I'm-- No. I have, I have--

25:22.303 --> 25:23.913
M-Mrs. Lyon, it's okay.
We-We're here to help you, okay?

25:23.957 --> 25:24.914
I don't need help.

25:24.958 --> 25:26.133
-I think you do.
-No.

25:26.176 --> 25:27.482
Let-Let's just--
We'll find a room

25:27.526 --> 25:29.266
and we can talk.

25:40.147 --> 25:42.149
Dorothy?

25:42.192 --> 25:43.933
Mrs. Lyon?

25:48.634 --> 25:51.637
I can't. I, uh,
have to be somewhere.

25:53.290 --> 25:54.988
Do you got a card I could have?

25:55.031 --> 25:56.380
[Joaquin]
Yes, ma'am.

25:56.424 --> 25:58.295
You were supposed to wait
in the truck.

25:58.339 --> 26:00.341
FBI is here.

26:00.384 --> 26:02.473
Look who they're talking to.

26:03.997 --> 26:05.781
Doesn't matter.
We got her husband.

26:05.825 --> 26:08.175
Had to tenderize him.

26:08.218 --> 26:10.090
What an asshole.

26:10.133 --> 26:11.961
Let's go.

26:16.575 --> 26:18.664
I'm Agent Joaquin.
This is my, this is my partner,

26:18.707 --> 26:20.274
-Agent Meyer. Here you go.
-Hey, there.

26:20.317 --> 26:21.710
We've been looking for you.

26:21.754 --> 26:23.451
Can you-- We just,
we just want to talk.

26:23.494 --> 26:25.801
-All right? Let's find a room.
-[elevator bell dings]

26:25.845 --> 26:27.890
-Yeah, a quiet room.
-You're okay, you're okay.

26:27.934 --> 26:30.153
-We're here to help you. Okay?
-It's okay.

26:30.197 --> 26:32.373
-I meant to ask, is your,
is your husband okay?
-Yeah.

26:32.416 --> 26:34.462
We went by the house.
That must've been some fire.

26:34.505 --> 26:35.594
He's...

26:37.726 --> 26:40.076
[narrator]
Only the tiger shark

26:40.120 --> 26:42.252
is a more dangerous foe.

26:42.296 --> 26:43.645
Though, of course,
the tiger shark,

26:43.689 --> 26:45.647
or any kind of shark, really,

26:45.691 --> 26:47.997
would suffocate
in a hospital setting.

26:51.697 --> 26:54.003
I'll just... I'll be quick.

26:58.921 --> 27:00.314
What do you think?

27:00.357 --> 27:01.794
She looks relieved.

27:01.837 --> 27:03.447
No more running.

27:03.491 --> 27:05.014
Honestly, I don't know how
she made it this far.

27:05.058 --> 27:06.973
Hmm.

27:08.365 --> 27:10.193
Have you seen a woman,

27:10.237 --> 27:12.761
like, light brown hair,
maybe five-two

27:12.805 --> 27:14.241
wearing nurse's scrubs?

27:14.284 --> 27:16.243
She's a biter.

27:16.286 --> 27:17.853
No. I can't help you.

27:17.897 --> 27:20.334
-Okay.
-Wait. What's her name?

27:20.377 --> 27:22.162
Mrs. Lyon?

27:23.859 --> 27:25.382
Dorothy?

27:31.824 --> 27:33.782
No more running?

27:35.175 --> 27:36.698
Well, shit.

27:43.487 --> 27:44.924
[sighs]

27:44.967 --> 27:47.013
[dogs barking outside]

27:49.058 --> 27:51.060
Mrs. Lyon.

27:51.104 --> 27:52.758
If I could just
understand better

27:52.801 --> 27:53.846
why you had her committed.

27:57.327 --> 27:58.764
You're a debtor.

27:59.982 --> 28:01.723
-What?
-I looked it up.

28:02.985 --> 28:05.988
$192,000.

28:06.032 --> 28:08.991
-[scoffs]
-Spread between your mortgage,

28:09.035 --> 28:12.168
car loans, your student loans,

28:12.212 --> 28:13.822
medical bills,

28:13.866 --> 28:15.302
credit cards.

28:15.345 --> 28:17.043
Hell, you've got it all.

28:17.086 --> 28:19.088
Th-That's not...

28:19.132 --> 28:20.960
I don't think...

28:21.003 --> 28:22.570
relevant to this.

28:23.745 --> 28:25.355
Don't feel bad.

28:25.399 --> 28:27.270
You're not alone.

28:27.314 --> 28:30.665
Over 90% of American adults
are debtors.

28:30.709 --> 28:32.711
In the red,
living beyond their means.

28:32.754 --> 28:34.277
Kids waiting in the wings.

28:34.321 --> 28:36.540
I-I'm not...

28:36.584 --> 28:39.152
I'm not that...
what you said.

28:39.195 --> 28:41.328
You see it, right?

28:41.371 --> 28:43.591
The cage you're in.

28:47.595 --> 28:48.988
I see it.

28:49.031 --> 28:50.467
What came first?

28:50.511 --> 28:52.818
Student loan?

28:52.861 --> 28:54.950
Mm. Let me guess.

28:57.257 --> 28:59.868
Your parents sent you
to a private school

28:59.912 --> 29:01.565
they can't afford,

29:01.609 --> 29:04.220
took out a loan, made you sign.

29:05.831 --> 29:07.658
I put myself through school,

29:07.702 --> 29:09.573
working two jobs.

29:09.617 --> 29:11.924
Mm, you got a loan.

29:11.967 --> 29:13.795
Tuition went up sophomore year.

29:13.839 --> 29:16.145
So, nobody tricked you
into debt,

29:16.189 --> 29:17.886
or-or forced you into it.

29:17.930 --> 29:19.714
You went willingly.

29:22.543 --> 29:24.675
At least the animals
in the zoo fight.

29:24.719 --> 29:27.548
I'm not an animal.

29:27.591 --> 29:30.116
But you're in the zoo.
All of you.

29:30.159 --> 29:31.944
And every month,

29:31.987 --> 29:34.033
the interest rate goes up,

29:34.076 --> 29:36.383
the fees and fines.

29:36.426 --> 29:38.472
You tuck your kids in at night,
never telling them

29:38.515 --> 29:40.039
that they're-they're
in the cage, too,

29:40.082 --> 29:42.128
because, when you die,

29:42.171 --> 29:44.608
your debts become theirs.

29:46.132 --> 29:47.655
So,

29:47.698 --> 29:49.352
just know that, when you

29:49.396 --> 29:52.268
talk to me, you're talking

29:52.312 --> 29:54.488
to the zookeeper.

29:55.489 --> 29:58.144
Not some lemming or lemur.

29:58.187 --> 29:59.841
Mrs. Lyon.

29:59.885 --> 30:02.452
Yes, I heard you.

30:02.496 --> 30:06.108
My psychotic...

30:06.152 --> 30:09.285
possibly homicidal
daughter-in-law

30:09.329 --> 30:13.594
escaped a locked
psychiatric ward.

30:13.637 --> 30:16.510
And what I want to know is,
are you gonna look for her,

30:16.553 --> 30:19.818
or are you gonna sit
drinking coffee in the one house

30:19.861 --> 30:22.037
in the state where I know
that girl ain't at?

30:32.178 --> 30:33.962
[man over radio]
Larson, are you there? Copy.

30:34.006 --> 30:35.964
[man 2]
Larson here. Copy.

30:42.884 --> 30:44.668
[whistles]

30:44.712 --> 30:46.888
[whispers] Hi.

30:47.889 --> 30:49.369
Mommy?

30:50.326 --> 30:52.067
[laughs]

30:54.026 --> 30:55.331
[exhales]

30:55.375 --> 30:57.594
I'm so happy to see you.

30:57.638 --> 31:00.336
-They said you were sick.
-Do I look sick?

31:00.380 --> 31:02.861
-You look tired.
-[snorts]

31:02.904 --> 31:04.645
Well, I'm right as rain
where it matters, so--

31:04.688 --> 31:07.082
-Mama?
-Yeah?

31:07.126 --> 31:08.997
Who's Sheriff Roy?

31:11.695 --> 31:14.089
Where did you hear that name?

31:14.133 --> 31:16.135
He was here at Grandma's.

31:17.353 --> 31:19.442
He said to say hi.

31:21.662 --> 31:23.011
He's no one.

31:24.970 --> 31:27.624
Just someone Mommy used to know.

31:27.668 --> 31:29.365
[whispers] Let's go.

31:29.409 --> 31:31.106
Come on, come on.

31:38.853 --> 31:40.507
[operative]
ID, please.

31:42.422 --> 31:44.032
But I'm leaving.

31:44.076 --> 31:46.382
-ID, please.
-Get out of my way.

31:46.426 --> 31:48.776
Sir, I have my orders.

31:48.819 --> 31:52.258
Nobody comes or goes
without showing ID.

31:52.301 --> 31:55.217
I hired you.
I sign your paychecks.

31:55.261 --> 31:57.219
That's who I am.

31:57.263 --> 31:59.221
I appreciate that, sir.

31:59.265 --> 32:01.832
I insist. ID, please.

32:01.876 --> 32:03.138
Uh...

32:10.580 --> 32:13.192
Thank you, Mr. Graves.

32:13.235 --> 32:14.758
Fuck you.

32:14.802 --> 32:16.804
Don't do this to me again.
Do you understand?

32:16.847 --> 32:18.632
-Have you seen Scotty?
-What?

32:18.675 --> 32:20.068
Scotty. She was just here.

32:20.112 --> 32:22.418
-[sighs]
-I can't find her.

32:22.462 --> 32:26.379
Well, I guess you'd better find
Mrs. Lyon's granddaughter.

32:27.684 --> 32:30.252
Toy box. 10-65.

32:30.296 --> 32:32.211
[operative 2]
Copy that, 10-65.
Moving your direction.

32:55.321 --> 32:56.975
Come on.

32:57.018 --> 32:58.628
Shit.

32:58.672 --> 33:00.369
[sighs]

33:19.040 --> 33:20.520
I made coffee.

33:21.477 --> 33:23.349
You want some?

33:31.531 --> 33:32.967
Why not?

33:33.011 --> 33:35.926
Looks like I'll be up
for a while.

33:37.363 --> 33:39.060
Hey, hon.

33:39.104 --> 33:42.368
We got half the force
looking for you. You okay?

33:42.411 --> 33:44.892
We had breakfast for dinner.

33:44.935 --> 33:47.590
[laughs softly] She loves that.

33:48.591 --> 33:50.071
Who doesn't?

33:58.427 --> 34:01.865
I added cinnamon
and a little honey.

34:03.215 --> 34:05.608
Didn't know you could do that.
Hmm.

34:05.652 --> 34:08.220
You got some cartoons
she could watch?

34:10.570 --> 34:14.052
Uh, they turned off
the cable last week...

34:16.271 --> 34:18.404
...but I think
there's a Little MermaidDVD

34:18.447 --> 34:21.494
-somewhere in the living room.
-Mm.

34:23.452 --> 34:25.063
How about that? Hmm?

34:25.106 --> 34:27.021
How does that sound?
Little Mermaid.

34:27.065 --> 34:29.458
-Princesses are dumb.
-[Dot laughs]

34:29.502 --> 34:31.547
But beggars can't be choosers.

34:31.591 --> 34:34.072
-Remote's on the table.
-Go on.

34:40.078 --> 34:43.342
I'm trying to think of who,
in the history of the world,

34:43.385 --> 34:45.735
has had a week
like the one you just had.

34:46.736 --> 34:48.869
Amelia Earhart, maybe.

34:48.912 --> 34:50.436
It's only been a week?

34:50.479 --> 34:52.264
Give or take.

34:52.307 --> 34:54.570
You got a nice face.

34:55.528 --> 34:57.182
You know that?

34:58.226 --> 34:59.836
Kind, in the eyes.

35:01.795 --> 35:04.450
Oh, I can be scary
when I need to.

35:04.493 --> 35:07.279
-Just ask my husband.
-Hmm.

35:07.322 --> 35:10.499
Is that him in the garage?

35:10.543 --> 35:13.111
What's he doing in there?
It's been hours.

35:13.154 --> 35:16.375
Yeah. The nine iron,
the eight iron, the seven iron.

35:16.418 --> 35:18.290
Don't get me started
on the putter.

35:18.333 --> 35:21.380
Ah. He's a golfer.

35:26.036 --> 35:29.692
You ever have a dream
where you, you wake up one day

35:29.736 --> 35:33.783
and you realize you're just
not tall enough to reach it?

35:34.828 --> 35:37.309
Well, he ain't woke up yet.

35:37.352 --> 35:40.703
Keeps thinking it's the gear.
"Maybe with better gear."

35:40.747 --> 35:43.750
So, every month when I open
the credit card bills,

35:43.793 --> 35:48.624
they just keep getting
bigger and bigger.

35:52.367 --> 35:53.629
Hm.

35:57.459 --> 36:00.593
I need to leave Scotty here
for a few days.

36:01.637 --> 36:03.509
You're not serious.

36:03.552 --> 36:06.294
-Two. Three, maybe, tops?
-[laughs softly]

36:07.252 --> 36:09.167
I got to do something.

36:09.210 --> 36:10.777
I don't...

36:12.039 --> 36:14.607
She's not safe at Lorraine's.

36:15.651 --> 36:17.697
Safe from what?

36:21.614 --> 36:23.659
[movie playing quietly]

36:41.199 --> 36:42.461
Price of admission.

36:43.679 --> 36:45.638
You tell me the truth,

36:45.681 --> 36:47.161
and I'll see if I can
help you out.

36:47.205 --> 36:48.249
[lighter clicks]

36:49.816 --> 36:51.296
Okay.

37:04.831 --> 37:08.356
Some fellas came for me
the other day,

37:08.400 --> 37:10.489
and again on Halloween.

37:11.490 --> 37:13.056
Who?

37:13.100 --> 37:15.668
My husband.

37:15.711 --> 37:17.235
The first one.

37:19.149 --> 37:21.108
Before Wayne.

37:22.109 --> 37:24.590
I was 17.

37:24.633 --> 37:26.809
15 when they took me in.

37:26.853 --> 37:29.682
That's a whole other story.

37:30.639 --> 37:32.162
Keep going.

37:38.995 --> 37:42.434
They never hit you when
it's going their way, you know?

37:44.958 --> 37:47.134
It's when they're weak,

37:47.177 --> 37:50.529
and just pretending
to be strong.

37:50.572 --> 37:53.967
When they need something small
to climb on to feel big.

37:56.665 --> 37:59.842
"They"? You said "they."

37:59.886 --> 38:01.540
-Can I just...
-[golf club thwacks]

38:05.283 --> 38:07.763
[whispers]
Can I leave her here or what?

38:09.722 --> 38:12.899
Dorothy... [sighs]

38:12.942 --> 38:14.901
You're a wanted fugitive.

38:14.944 --> 38:18.121
Your daughter is a missing
person, presumed kidnapped,

38:18.165 --> 38:20.559
and I'm an officer
of the law. I...

38:20.602 --> 38:22.387
-So that's a no?
-[door closes]

38:22.430 --> 38:25.085
[Lars]
Babe, I'm slicing right again.

38:25.128 --> 38:27.348
It's those goddamn clubs
that Walter sold me.

38:27.392 --> 38:29.132
I'm gonna take them back
in the morning,

38:29.176 --> 38:31.178
see if he'll exchange them
for the Epic MAX Star five,

38:31.221 --> 38:34.486
but we need to be prepared
for him to bone me.

38:36.444 --> 38:38.490
Babe, there's a lady
in our kitchen.

38:38.533 --> 38:40.492
There sure is.

38:44.409 --> 38:46.976
This is my friend Alice,
from the potlucks

38:47.020 --> 38:48.848
over at Saint Luke's.

38:50.023 --> 38:53.069
Hi. Forgive the getup.

38:53.113 --> 38:55.333
I just pulled a double
at the hospital.

38:55.376 --> 38:57.726
Hey.

39:01.339 --> 39:02.992
Her daughter Scotty's gonna be
staying with us

39:03.036 --> 39:05.691
for a couple of days.

39:05.734 --> 39:09.085
She's in the living room,
watching The Little Mermaid.

39:11.479 --> 39:13.568
Like, an actual kid?

39:14.526 --> 39:16.571
♪ ♪

39:32.979 --> 39:34.459
[engine starts]

39:57.786 --> 39:59.875
♪ ♪

42:19.145 --> 42:22.061
[man]
Now I get it.

42:22.104 --> 42:24.193
[rooster crows]

42:28.154 --> 42:28.197
[roars]
